### Description

This issue seems identical to [ComponentRef<T> onDestroyed() callback does not get called ](https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/39365) except that I create components dynamically with  `createComponent` instead of `ComponentFactoryResolver` . Here is my reproduction code:

    @Component({ ... })
    export class AppComponent implements AfterViewInit {
       @ViewChild('container') c: ElementRef;
       showFoo = true;

      constructor(
          private appRef: ApplicationRef,
          private injector: Injector,
          private envInjector: EnvironmentInjector ) {}

      ngAfterViewInit() {
          const ref = createComponent(FooComponent, {
             environmentInjector: this.envInjector,
             elementInjector: this.injector,
             hostElement: this.c.nativeElement,
         });

         this.appRef.attachView(ref.hostView);
      }

In the component's HTML I can remove the dynamically created component as follows

    <button (click)="showFoo = false">cleanup</button>

    <div *ngIf="showFoo" #container></div>

Now, when the `app-foo` component is removed from the view, its `ngOnDestroy` method is not called. This issue also occurs, for example, if the parent component is removed in which components were rendered this way (dynamically)
 


