### Description

The current `Provider` disponible for us are, most of the time, static, meaning that it couldn't be changed in runtime, only overwritten or used as a multiple value, the proposed solution brings an opportunity to have a `Provider`that could have its own value redefined in runtime

### Proposed solution

it would be amazing to have a provider that assign it's own value every time it's called, it coluld be declared the same as a FactoryProvider, but instead of assigning once when the module/component/injectable is created, it would assign every it's called like shown below

```TypeScript
@Service({
  providedIn: 'root'
})
export class SomeService {
  value: string = 'default' // <== mutable value
}

@NgModule({
  ...
  providers: [
    {
      provide: 'BAR',
      deps: [SomeService],
      useFunction: (ss: SomeService) => {
        return ss.value || 'value'
      },
    }
  ]
})

@Component({
  ....
})
export class FooComponent {
  constructor(@Inject('BAR') private bar: string) {}
  
  doSomething(): void {
    console.log(this.bar) // <== This should get the value everey time its called
  }
}

```

### Alternatives considered

Also, with the `FactoryResolver` itself could be used as shown above with it's own value being reassigned every time that it's called in the app

